headline: Did Altria's (MO) Dividend Hike and KT&G Deal Signal a New Strategic Direction?
summary: Earlier this week, Altria raised its quarterly dividend by 3.9%, marking the 60th increase in the past 56 years, and entered a Memorandum of Understanding with KT&G Corporation to explore opportunities in modern oral nicotine products and efficiency-driven projects. This move signals Altria’s ongoing commitment to dividend growth while also targeting new international markets and product categories with its KT&G collaboration.
